It seems Preferences#propertyNames() returned an array containing null elements.
Looking into its implementation, it seems that after the result array has been
created, one element may have been removed from properties, thus causing the
array to have more positions than actual elements.

public String[] propertyNames() {
	String[] result = new String[properties.size()];
	properties.keySet().toArray(result);
	return result;
}

Shouldn't the preferences object be thread safe?

DJ, this would be something to take into consideration in the new preferences
mechanism work.

A simple fix to make it thread safe, at the expense of an extra object creation:

public String[] propertyNames() {
	return (String[])properties.keySet().toArray(new String[0]);
}
